 \"to\": 2132}, {\"ngram\": \"the possibility\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2157}, {\"ngram\": \"Mathys Tel\", \"from\": 2162, \"to\": 2172}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I know it seems quite simple, quite cold, but that's exactly what happened.'\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2265, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"GOALKEEPERS:Lucas Chevalier (Lille), Guillaume Restes (Toulouse), Obed Nkambadio (Paris FC), Robin Risser (Strasbourg) DEFENDERS:Bafode Diakite (Lille), Maxime Esteve (Burnley), Bradley Locko (Brest), Castello Lukeba (RB Leipzig), Kiliann Sildillia (Freiburg), Adrien Truffert (Rennes), Lenny Yoro (Lille) MIDFIELDERS:Maghnes Akliouche (Monaco), Joris Chotard (Montpellier), Desire Doue (Rennes), Manu Kone (Borussia Monchengladbach), Khephren Thuram (Nice), Enzo Millot (Stuttgart), Lesley Ugochukwu (Chelsea), Warren Zaire-Emery (PSG) ATTACKERS:Bradley Barcola (PSG), Arnaud Kalimuendo (Rennes), Alexandre Lacazette (Lyon), Jean-Philippe Mateta (Crystal Palace), Michael Olise (Crystal Palace), Mathys Tel (Bayern Munich) When asked why Chelsea have released Ugochukwu but not Gusto, Henry replied: 'Ask them.\", \"from\": 2267, \"to\": 3082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2279, \"end\": 2284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lucas_Horton\", \"score\": 0.8444934810088628, \"rank\": 0.1841353646058559, \"text\": \"Lucas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lucas_Horton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lucas_Horton\"}, {\"begin\": 2333, \"end\": 2337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Obed_(biblical_figure)\", \"score\": 0.9259521582560615, \"rank\": 0.04152249134948316, \"text\": \"Obed\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Obed_(biblical_figure)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Obed_(biblical_figure)\"}, {\"begin\": 2349, \"end\": 2357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_FC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.680634558542147e-52, \"text\": \"Pari